snippet.title: Harry Maguire reveals to Gary Neville why he chose United over City, EURO hopes & more | The Overlap

localized.title: Harry Maguire reveals to Gary Neville why he chose United over City, EURO hopes & more | The Overlap
localized.description:
A few weeks ago I had the pleasure of speaking to Manchester United Captain Harry Maguire.

Harry talks about what it was like breaking through at Sheffield United, and which defenders inspired him as a kid. 

We reflect on England, talking about the experience of Russia in 2018, and the heart-breaking loss against Croatia. He even reveals why he turned up to the England squad with bin bags!

I find out why Harry chose United over City, and then what it’s been like becoming Captain of Manchester United.

I give him a special handwritten letter from Sir Alex Ferguson, and then we get stuck into a putting challenge!

Let me know in the comments if you enjoyed this episode, and who do you want to see on next?

Brought to you exclusively by Sky Bet.

0:00-9:59 The inspiration of Ferdinand & Terry, breaking through at Sheffield United, and the England bin-bags
10:00-17:02 Getting called up to England, losing against Croatia and looking ahead to the EUROs
17:02-29:21 Choosing Manchester United over Manchester City, the impact of social media and becoming United Captain
29:21-42:23 Harry’s lowest point of his career, VAR, a letter from Sir Alex and a putting challenge!

snippet.title: Toto Wolff's "Cross Threaded" Claim Explained

localized.title: Toto Wolff's "Cross Threaded" Claim Explained
localized.description:
During the 2021 Formula 1 Monaco Grand Prix, Valtteri Bottas pitted but his front right tyre couldn't come off his car. After the race, Toto Wolff claimed the wheel nut had cross threaded, so here's an explainer of what cross threading is!

At the time of making the video, Toto had said that the pit crew had cross threaded the wheel nut, which I took as the fact and based the video around that.
But since the video has been released, Mercedes have now said that the wheel gun had machined the nut removing the driving faces.

So rather than the thread being ripped to shreds, it was actually the nut itself - Apologies for getting it wrong but hopefully you've learnt a bit about cross threading 😅

snippet.title: Painting on CLAY

localized.title: Painting on CLAY
localized.description:
Hey guys! Today I wanted to try something a little bit different. I decided to try sculpting with Das air dry clay. I wanted to make some original clay creations and paint them myself. I feel like it's so satisfying to watch sculpting and then painting on clay. I've seen those tiktok clay painting videos hahah. So this has been on my video idea list for a long time. I am very much so a beginner when it comes to clay, so I wanted to stick to some fun and easy things to make with air dry clay. I think air dry clay is much more beginner friendly than polymer clay, and I really enjoyed working with this brand. Although, of course, the most fun part of creating things with clay, is painting and decorating the clay in the end. I ended up making some cute, custom clay figurines, I hope you like them!

snippet.title: VW Golf R Mk8 v Mk7.5: DRAG RACE

localized.title: VW Golf R Mk8 v Mk7.5: DRAG RACE
localized.description:
Need help buying your next car? Click the following link and my team and I will help you choose your ideal car at a fair price - from Mat Watson! http://bit.ly/-Help-Me-carwow
.............................................................

Who’s up for a Golf R drag race! 

We’ve brought in the all-new Mk8 Golf R to go up against its older brother, the Mk7, to see which is the fastest over the quarter-mile. 

As you’d suspect, there’s very little to split them when you look at the stats on paper. Starting with the Mk8, it’s powered by a 2-litre turbocharged 4 cylinder petrol engine, which delivers 320hp & 420Nm. It weighs in at 1,551kg, and costs from around £39,000. 

As for the Mk7, well it’s also powered by a 2-litre turbocharged 4 cylinder petrol engine, although it only puts down 300hp and 400Nm. It does weigh slightly less though, coming in at 1,483kg. This is largely down to the newer Golf R having a more advanced AWD system, however.

So what do you think - will the Mk8 walk it? There’s only one way to find out… LET’S RACE!

The breathtaking, generation-defining Broadway phenomenon becomes a soaring cinematic event as Tony, Grammy and Emmy Award winner Ben Platt reprises his role as an anxious, isolated high schooler aching for understanding and belonging amid the chaos and cruelty of the social-media age.   

Directed by acclaimed filmmaker Stephen Chbosky (The Perks of Being A Wallflower, Wonder), the film is written for the screen by the show’s Tony winner Steven Levenson with music and lyrics by the show’s Oscar®, Grammy and Tony-winning songwriting team of Benj Pasek & Justin Paul (La La Land, The Greatest Showman). 

Featuring Grammy winning songs, including the iconic anthem “You Will Be Found,” “Waving Through a Window,” “For Forever” and “Words Fail,” Dear Evan Hansen stars six-time Oscar® nominee Amy Adams, Oscar® winner Julianne Moore, Kaitlyn Dever (Booksmart), Amandla Stenberg (The Hate U Give), Colton Ryan (Apple TV+’s Little Voice), Nik Dodani (Netflix’s Atypical), DeMarius Copes (Broadway’s Mean Girls) and Danny Pino (NBC’s Law & Order: Special Victims Unit). 

Dear Evan Hansen is produced by Marc Platt (La La Land, Into the Woods, Mary Poppins Returns) and Adam Siegel (2 Guns, Drive), and is executive produced by Michael Bederman, Steven Levenson, Benj Pasek and Justin Paul. Universal Pictures will distribute the film in all territories.
